	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_3SKOLA">
			<Text>[ICON_HAPPINESS_1] Hogskola</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_3SKOLA_TEXT">
			<Text>
				Swedish state schools are funded by tax money. This goes for both primary and secondary schools, high schools and universities. When studying at a university, however, you might have to pay for accommodation and literature. There are private schools as well who also receive funding from the government, but they may charge a fee from the parents.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]The alpine tundra has been a target of research by the hydrological research groups as well as the Departments of Zoology and Botany at Stockholm University. The Ekoklim program comprises, among other things, studies of climate and hydrology in tundra regions, and impacts of climate change on the tundra biota. The tundra is not a cold and useless wasteland. It is a very fragile environment and the plants and animals that have made their home on the tundra biome have made some incredible adaptations to the long, cold winters and the short but abundant summers.
			</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_3SKOLA_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Hogskola is a Swedish unique building that replaces the University. It yields +33% [ICON_RESEARCH] Science in the City. Allows training of Archaeologists in the city. Tundra and Jungles tiles yield an additional 2 [ICON_RESEARCH] Science.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_3SKOLA_HELP">
			<Text>Increases the amount of [ICON_RESEARCH] Science of a city. Additional [ICON_RESEARCH] Science from Jungle and Tundra tiles.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>

